>thanks for your reply.
>
>Let me put it this way:
>
>I have a rectangle(2d). I know the bottom left corner of the 
>rectangle as the origin. Also i know the length and height of the 
>rectangle.My question is how do i calculate the length of an arbitary 
>point on this rectangle.Inother word what will be the general 
>equation of finding the length of an arbitary point on this rectangle.
>
>bye.
>

Points don't have length.  Do you mean the distance from this
arbitrary point to ... some other point, such as the origin?  If that,
then the distance is

  sqrt( x^2 + y^2 ).

